Column.name: Note
Column.value: Instruction to pay an amount of money to an ultimate beneficiary, on behalf of an originator. (ISO20022)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Instruction to execute a payment from a payer to a payee

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A specific relationship between a specific Bank (= party acting as a supplier of banking services) and one or more other involved parties acting as (potential) consumers of banking services as agreed in one or more banking product or service offerings and/or agreements.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
A planned or performed action in the context of concluding or fulfilling an agreement.
Act to do something.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: An act, initiated by the payer or payee, of placing, transferring or withdrawing funds, irrespective of any underlying obligations between the payer and payee (a proposed definition for BIAN BOM adapted from PSD)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A classification of an instance of a payment instruction as an inbound or outbound payment.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
Classification of a payment instruction according to the arrangement type that made it possible/generated it
There are several ways a payment instruction can be created - as a consequence of the fulfillment of an arrangement ("a "xxx-FulfillmentEvent" (a standing order instruction is also the fulfillment of an arrangement) - as an instruction given by a customer (made possible by a payment service arrangement), e.g. a credit transfer, a card payment, a withdrawal, a deposit, a direct debit instruction.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The payment system requested to be used in a payment instruction.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Type of critical dates of a payment transaction executed by the payment order like RequestedExecutionDate.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
Classification of the Money Transfer Instruction according to the event that lead to the instruction
e.g. withdrawal, interest disbursement, direct debit, card payment.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Amount of money to be transferred.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Currency in which the transfer amount is expressed.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
The reason why the instruction is given
can be reference to a lot of information, concerning e.g. a purchase, an arrangement fulfillment event, a billing period...

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The network to be used for the processing of the money transfer instruction as requested in the instruction. e.g. instant SEPA?

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The processing status of the instruction

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Reference to the contact channel that was used to give the money transfer instruction

Column.name: Note
Column.value: An identifier that allows to uniquely refer to an instance of a transaction.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The Date that the transaction has occurred or is planned to occur. A characteristic of transaction which refers to the LifecycleDate of transaction (e.g., initiated date, executed date, fulfillment date).

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Specifies the category of Transaction like payment transaction, accounting transaction, financial Transaction, banking transaction, etc.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A detailed explanation or commentary of transaction.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A characteristic of transaction which refers to the LifecycleStatus of transaction (e.g., initiated, executed, confirmed, cancelled, etc.)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The name of transaction.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: An identifier that allows to uniquely refer to a Payment Transaction.

Column.value: The payment mechanism the bank decides to use in the transaction to execute a payment instruction
